15/12/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The year-long EU police mission Proxima officially kicks off Monday (15 December), replacing the military force Concordia. 
The EU police are to train local police to improve the security situation, improve their relations with the public, and help advance the fight against organised crime.
In other news, the city of Ohrid hosted a two-day international conference on minority rights, starting Friday. 
Macedonian President Boris Trajkovski and EU Special Representative in Skopje Alexis Brouhns took part in the discussions. 
(MIA - 14/12/03; Makfax - 12/12/03)
